<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Jones, John. Letter to Judge Adam Mabane, 1787, with a copy of Jones's testimony 1783. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0003</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">same thing as to file a blank sheet of Paper.  Further.  To shew that it was <span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span> and regularly <span style="text-decoration:underline;">filed</span>, you should prove that M<sup>r</sup> Williams had received Communication of <span class="DelHand-author">M<sup>r</sup> Panet objections</span> <span class="AddHand-author">it</span>:</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">You should on the 11th June, have received <span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span> &amp; <span style="text-decoration:underline;">filed</span> the defence <span class="AddHand-author">or objections, and heard the argument </span>of M<sup>r</sup> Cochrane, <span class="DelHand-author">then have ordered</span> <span class="AddHand-author">after hearing his reply then you should have ordered </span>Communication to be given to M<sup>r</sup> Williams, and then have <span style="text-decoration:underline;">considered of the same</span>, &amp; not before. <span class="AddHand-author">Were these things done? No.</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">This must carry conviction with it that your own Testimony of Record makes against &amp; condems you; but to the full refutation of your malicious Charge, I bring such Oral prooff, in support of my evidence, and in contradiction to your Comments, that no Man living can challenge or doubt:  I annex to this Letter a Copy of an Original Paper, now in my possession, dated the 8th Instant, being the declaration of M<sup>r</sup> J. A. Panet Advocate, &amp; M<sup>r</sup> Jaques Perrault Merchant in the French Language and of M<sup>r</sup> John Blackwood in the English Language made in the presence of seven Gentlemen of Character &amp; Consequence, besides two Gentlemen of the Bar, <span style="text-decoration:underline;">which</span> will be confirmed by oath in a Court of Justice.</p>
<p class="head">This Declaration sets forth,</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">That, M<sup>r</sup> Panet advocate for the Defendant M<sup>r</sup> Cochrane came to Court with a written Paper, containing his Client's Defence against a Motion, made the preceding Court day by M<sup>r</sup> Williams, shewing cause why it should no be granted.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">JJ</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[7]</span></p>

